  $( Cancellation law for addition.  Theorem I.1 of Apostol, p. 18.  This
     proof illustrates how ~ dedth3h can be used to convert
     the assumptions of ~ addcan into antecedents.  This general
     method can be used to convert deductions into theorems as needed. $)
  addcant $p |- ( ( A e. CC /\ B e. CC /\ C e. CC ) ->
                ( ( A + B ) = ( A + C ) <-> B = C ) ) $=
    ( cc wcel caddc co wceq wb cn0 cded opreq1 cleq12d birbid opreq2 cleq1d
    cleq1 bi2bid cleq2d cleq2 0cn elimel addcan dedth3h ) ADEZBDEZCDEZABFGZACFG
    ZHZBCHZIUEAJKZBFGZULCFGZHZUKIABCJJJULUFBJKZFGZUNHZUPCHZIUQULUGCJKZFGZHZUPUT
